1
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:19,640
Danger!

2
00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:21,680
This is a warning.

3
00:00:21,760 --> 00:00:25,000
A warning to the whole world.
You're looking for wi-fi.

4
00:00:30,960 --> 00:00:32,200
Sometimes you see something...

5
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:36,800
a bit like this.

6
00:00:40,960 --> 00:00:42,480
Don't click it.

7
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:44,200
Do not click it.

8
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:49,000
Once you've clicked it,
they're in your computer.

9
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,480
(BEEPING)

10
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:52,320
They can see you.

11
00:00:52,880 --> 00:00:55,760
If they can see you,
they might choose you.

12
00:00:56,680 --> 00:00:58,880
And if they do, you die.

13
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:03,280
In 24 hours, you're dead.

14
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:05,040
For a while.

15
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:08,560
People's souls are being
uploaded to the internet.

16
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:10,000
Some people get stuck.

17
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:12,680
Their minds,
their souls, trapped in the wi-fi.

18
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:14,040
MAN: (ECHOING) I don't know where I am.

19
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:17,960
Like echoes, like ghosts.
Sometimes you can hear their screams,

20
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:21,600
on the radio,
on the telly or on the net.

21
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:24,320
WOMAN 1: I don't know where I am.
WOMAN 2: I don't know where I am.

22
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,560
-This is real. This is not a hoax...
-WOMAN 3: Please help me.

23
00:01:26,800 --> 00:01:27,960
I don't know where I am.

24
00:01:28,080 --> 00:01:29,680
-...or a joke...
-(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

25
00:01:29,880 --> 00:01:31,680
-...or a story.
-I don't know where I am.

26
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,640
This is real and I know that.

27
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:37,920
(VOICE BREAKING)
'Cause I don't know where I am.

28
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:39,560
Please.

29
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:44,000
Please, if... If you can hear me...

30
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:47,840
If you can hear me,
I don't know where I am.

31
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:50,960
ALL: (OVERLAPPING)
I don't know where I am.

32
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:54,480
(ALL TALKING AT ONCE)

33
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:59,640
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

34
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:45,160
Wake the Abbot,
the bells of Saint John are ringing.

35
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:47,920
(BELL TOLLING)

36
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:55,960
We must go to him.

37
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,880
They call him the Mad Monk, don't they?

38
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,120
They shouldn't.

39
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:08,640
He's definitely not a monk.

40
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,760
(CLEARS THROAT)

41
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:15,160
I'm sorry to intrude.

42
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:17,600
The bells of Saint John are ringing.

43
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:27,680
I'm going to need a horse.

44
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:39,880
Is that her?

45
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,600
The woman twice dead.

46
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:45,280
And her final message.

47
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:50,840
He has withdrawn to this place
of peace and solitude

48
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:53,000
that he might divine her meaning.

49
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,280
If he truly is mad,

50
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:58,000
then this is his madness.

51
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,560
Angie? Is the internet working?

52
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,880
I'm trying to phone the helpline,
they won't answer.

53
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:08,120
-It's working for me.
-Can I use it when you're finished?

54
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:11,120
More than one person can use
the internet at a time, Clara.

55
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,400
-You doing your homework?
-Shut up, you're not my mum.

56
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:14,920
And I'm not trying to be, okay?

57
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,120
Right.

58
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:21,480
Yes! Angie's probably fine on her own.
You could probably have the night off.

59
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:24,360
I'm okay. I'll be upstairs trying
to figure out my computer.

60
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:27,520
Anyway, the adverts are in.
So, hopefully, we'll find someone.

61
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:29,120
I'm here as long as you need me.

62
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:32,440
GEORGE: Good. Right.
Come on, Artie. Time to go.

63
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:35,760
-What chapter are you on?
-Ten.

64
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:38,600
(GASPS) Eleven is the best.
You'll cry your eyes out.

65
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:40,200
GEORGE: Artie!

66
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,920
Oh, come on! Just answer.

67
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:48,840
Just pick it up. Pick it up. Pick it up.
Pick it up. Pick it up.

68
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,280
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

69
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:34,240
(RINGING CONTINUES)

70
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,960
That is not supposed to happen.

71
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:51,440
(RINGING CONTINUES)

72
00:05:56,640 --> 00:06:00,120
-Hello?
-Ah, hello! I can't find the internet.

73
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,560
-Sorry?
-It's gone. The internet.

74
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:04,040
Can't find it anywhere. Where is it?

75
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,800
-The internet?
-Yes, the internet.

76
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:08,520
Why don't I have the internet?

77
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,240
It's 1207.

78
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:17,200
I've got half past three.
Am I phoning a different time zone?

79
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:19,200
Yeah, you really sort of are.

80
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:21,200
-Will it show up on the bill?
-Oh, I dread to think.

81
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:23,440
Listen, where did you get this number?

82
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:26,760
The woman in the shop wrote it down.
It's a helpline, isn't it?

83
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:29,480
She said it's the best helpline
out there. In the universe, she said.

84
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,360
What woman? Who was she?

85
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:33,400
I don't know. The woman in the shop.

86
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:37,760
So, why isn't there internet?
Shouldn't it just sort of be there?

87
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:40,480
Look, listen. I'm not actually...
This isn't...

88
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:44,560
You have clicked on the wi-fi button,
haven't you?

89
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,520
Hang on. Um...

90
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:51,160
Wi-fi...

91
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:54,920
Click on the wi-fi,
you'll see a list of names.

92
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,080
-You see one you recognise...
-It's asking me for a password.

93
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,080
Is it okay if I go and see Nina?

94
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:01,840
-You can call her mum.
-Sure.

95
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,120
Um, what's the password
for the internet?

96
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:05,080
R-Y-C-B-A-R-1-2-3.

97
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:07,800
-How am I supposed to remember that?
-(SIGHS)

98
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:12,520
-Is it an evil spirit?
-It's a woman.

99
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,120
Hang on. Just a mo.

100
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:20,760
Run you clever boy and remember...

101
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:22,960
One...

102
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,600
Run, you clever boy...

103
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:27,720
Two...

104
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,800
...and remember.

105
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,920
-Three...
-What did you say?

106
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:35,320
Don't shout!

107
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,640
Now you made me type it wrong.
It's thrown me out again.

108
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:40,760
What do I do? How do I get back in?

109
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:58,440
It's just a, um,
a thing to remember the password,

110
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,680
"run you clever boy and remember”.

111
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:02,680
-(PEOPLE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)
-Hang on.

112
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:05,440
(WOMAN SOBBING, ALL TALKING AT ONCE)

113
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:12,840
-(BANGING ON DOOR)
-Hello, yes!

114
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:14,720
-(DOORBELL RINGING CONTINUOUSLY)
-I hear you!

115
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,000
Yep!

116
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:17,640
Uh-huh!

117
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:19,480
Hello?

118
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:22,160
(PANTING) Clara.

119
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,640
Clara Oswald?

120
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,040
-Hello.
-Clara Oswin Oswald!

121
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:26,960
Just Clara Oswald.
What was that middle one?

122
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:28,760
Do you remember me?

123
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:33,560
-No. Should I? Who are you?
-The Doctor.

124
00:08:34,040 --> 00:08:35,840
No? The Doctor?

125
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:40,760
-Doctor who?
-No, just The Doctor.

126
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:42,000
Actually, sorry.

127
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:43,560
-Could you just ask me that again?
-Could I what?

128
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,920
Could you just ask me
that question again?

129
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,120
Doctor who?

130
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:48,800
-Okay, just once more.
-Doctor who?

131
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:50,360
Oh, yeah.

132
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,160
Ooh...

133
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:56,840
Do you know, I never realise how much
I enjoy hearing that said out loud.

134
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,440
-Thank you.
-Okay.

135
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:00,360
Hey! No! Clara!

136
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:03,640
Please! Clara, I need to talk to you!

137
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:04,960
(BANGING ON DOOR)

138
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,960
Listen! Please!

139
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,880
ALEXEI: Clara Oswald.

140
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:13,600
We've got a positive lock on her
but I think she's borderline.

141
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:15,560
Very clever but no computer skills.

142
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:18,600
Upload her anyway.
Splice her a computer skills package.

143
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:20,240
I'll activate a spoon head.

144
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:23,320
Alexei, we call them servers,
not spoon heads.

145
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:25,040
Sorry, Miss Kizlet.

146
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:28,760
I'm ever so fond of Alexei.

147
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:31,760
But my conscience says
we should probably kill him.

148
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:33,560
I'll inform HR.

149
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:35,760
Actually, he's about to go on holiday.

150
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:38,880
Kill him when he gets back.
Let's not be unreasonable.

151
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:41,080
Didn't you want to speak to me?

152
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:43,080
We're uploading
too many people too quickly,

153
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:45,160
we're going to get noticed.

154
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:48,440
If your conscience is bothering you,
think of it like this.

155
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:52,000
We're preserving living minds
in permanent form in the data cloud.

156
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:54,160
It's like immortality.

157
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:57,200
-Only fatal.
-My conscience is fine.

158
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:00,800
Good. Because our client has his needs.

159
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:03,400
(TABLET TONE WHOOSHES)

160
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:12,320
Did you just hack me?

161
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,920
Because you changed your mind?

162
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:17,280
I hope I did.

163
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,560
(WHOOSHING)

164
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:29,760
DOCTOR: Please!
I just need to speak to you.

165
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:41,040
Why are you still here?
Why are you here at all?

166
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:43,880
Oi, you phoned me.
You were looking for the internet.

167
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:46,000
-That was you?
-Of course it was me.

168
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,160
How did you get here so fast?

169
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:49,360
I just happened to be
in the neighbourhood

170
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,440
on my mobile phone!

171
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:53,800
When you say "mobile phone”,
why did you point at that blue box?

172
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:56,920
Because it's a surprisingly
accurate description.

173
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,960
Okay. We're finished now.

174
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:00,920
Oi, no! Look...

175
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,600
(DOOR SLAMS)

176
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:07,320
(FLOOR CREAKING)

177
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,400
Angie?

178
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:13,080
Angie, are you upstairs?

179
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:15,280
(CREAKING CONTINUES)

180
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:17,520
Angie, are you still here?

181
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:22,320
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

182
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:34,320
Hello.

183
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,600
Hello.

184
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:40,440
Are you a friend of Angie's?

185
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:44,240
I'm a friend of Angie's.

186
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:47,280
What were you doing upstairs?

187
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:49,800
I was upstairs.

188
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:55,920
I know you, don't I?

189
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,720
You know me. Don't you?

190
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,240
(GASPS)

191
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,240
(WHIRRING)

192
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,960
(ELECTRONIC BEEPING)

193
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:29,520
Right! Don't be a monk!

194
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:34,880
Monks are not cool!

195
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:40,960
Ah!

196
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:43,240
(LAUGHS EXCITEDLY)

197
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:12,400
Ha! Clara! (KNOCKING)

198
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:13,800
-Clara?
-Hello?

199
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:15,880
(CHUCKLES) See, look it's me.

200
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:18,640
De-monked. Sensible clothes.

201
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:20,880
Um, can I come in now?

202
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,840
-I don't understand.
-Could you just open the door?

203
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:23,920
I don't know...

204
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:25,520
Of course you can.

205
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,680
...where I am.

206
00:13:27,760 --> 00:13:29,000
(CLARA BREATHING HEAVILY)

207
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:30,840
I don't know where I am/!

208
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:32,640
Where am I?

209
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:35,080
Please tell me where I am.
I don't know where I am/!

210
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:37,080
-(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)
-I don't know where I am/!

211
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:38,560
-I don't know where I am.
-Clara!

212
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:40,640
-Clara?
-(BREATHING HEAVILY)

213
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:42,960
CLARA: (PANICKED)
I don't know where I am.

214
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:44,840
I don't know where I am/!

215
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:47,400
I don't understand.
I don't know where I am.

216
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:49,280
I don't know where I am.
I don't understand.

217
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:50,400
I don't know where I am/!

218
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:52,760
(PANTING) Where am I?

219
00:13:53,560 --> 00:13:55,160
I don't know where I am.

220
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:56,680
-(WHIRRING)
-I don't know where I am.

221
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:58,680
I don't know where I am.

222
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,840
(ALARM BLARING)

223
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,120
I've got a problem.

224
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:09,920
(WHIRRING)

225
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:17,360
Walking base station.

226
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:20,760
Walking wi-fi base station.
Hoovering up data,

227
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,560
hoovering up people!

228
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:28,040
Oh, no, you don't!

229
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,480
Oh, no, you don't.

230
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:37,400
Looks like someone's trying
to reverse an upload.

231
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:38,560
KIZLET: Is that possible?

232
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:41,320
If the upload isn't fully
integrated yet. In theory, yes.

233
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:45,680
(ALARM BEEPING)

234
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:48,320
Oh, my God.

235
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:53,640
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

236
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:56,680
Not this time, Clara. I promise you.

237
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:07,160
MAHLER: Can you stop this?

238
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:09,640
No.

239
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:21,360
(SPOONHEAD WHIRRING)

240
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:29,400
(GASPING)

241
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:31,200
-(COUGHING)
-Okay.

242
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:33,880
It's okay. It's okay.
You're fine. You're back.

243
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:35,720
Yes, you are.

244
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:37,680
Oh, yes, you are.

245
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,520
Well?

246
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:48,200
Our hacker sent us a message.

247
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:54,320
MAHLER: I assume
he's talking about the girl.

248
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:57,440
Get out.

249
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,680
I have to speak to the client.

250
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:12,320
Sir.

251
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:15,760
The one you told me about, he's here.

252
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:18,040
The Doctor is here.

253
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:30,400
Ha.

254
00:16:33,840 --> 00:16:35,160
(SNIFFS)

255
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:37,520
Mmm.

256
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:42,400
Mmm.

257
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,720
(SIGHS)

258
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,960
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDING)

259
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:56,960
(FRONT DOOR CLOSES)

260
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:01,760
(DOG BARKING)

261
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:08,440
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

262
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:10,160
Hello?

263
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:12,400
Hello!

264
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:15,160
Are you all right?

265
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:16,760
-I'm in bed.
-Yes.

266
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,320
-I don't remember going.
-No.

267
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:20,080
-What did I miss?
-Oh!

268
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:22,600
Quite a lot, actually. Uh...

269
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:23,960
Angie called.

270
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:27,160
She'd going to stay over at Nina's.
Apparently that's all completely fine

271
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:28,560
and you shouldn't worry
like you always do,

272
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:30,160
for God's sake, get off her back.

273
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:31,760
Also, your dad phoned.

274
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:34,120
Mainly about the government,
he seems very cross with them.

275
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:37,480
I've got several pages on that.
I said I'd look into it.

276
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:39,680
I fixed that rattling noise
in the washing machine,

277
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:41,080
indexed the kitchen cupboards,

278
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:43,360
optimised the photosynthesis
in the main flower bed

279
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:45,720
-and assembled the quadricycle.
-Assembled the what?

280
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:48,040
I found a disassembled quadricycle
in the garage.

281
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:49,160
I don't think you did.

282
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,160
I invented the quadricycle!

283
00:18:53,360 --> 00:18:54,880
(CHUCKLES)

284
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:59,120
What happened to me?

285
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:00,720
Don't you remember?

286
00:19:03,160 --> 00:19:05,400
I was scared. Really scared.

287
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:09,200
Didn't know where I was.

288
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:12,320
-Do you know now?
-Yes.

289
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:15,120
Well, then, you should go to sleep.

290
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:18,360
Because you're safe now, I promise.

291
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:20,840
Goodnight, Clara.

292
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:31,480
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

293
00:19:31,560 --> 00:19:34,400
-Are you guarding me?
-Well, yes.

294
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:35,920
Yes, I am.

295
00:19:39,280 --> 00:19:41,320
Are you seriously going to
sit down there all night?

296
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:43,880
Yeah, I promise.
I won't budge from this spot.

297
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:48,440
Well, then, I'll have to come to you.

298
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:49,800
Eh?

299
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:57,000
- I take it the girl's inside and alive?
-Yes.

300
00:19:58,760 --> 00:19:59,960
Alexei,

301
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:04,480
I need you to do
something creative about that.

302
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:07,120
(ALEXEI TYPING, COMPUTER BEEPING)

303
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:12,760
-I like your house.
-It isn't mine.

304
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:15,160
-I'm a friend of the family.
-You look after the kids.

305
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:17,960
Oh, yes. You're a governess, aren't you?
Just like...

306
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:19,760
Just like what?

307
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:24,240
Just like...
I thought you probably would be.

308
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:26,480
Are you gonna explain
what happened to me?

309
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:32,440
There's something in the wi-fi.

310
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:35,200
-Okay.
-This whole world is swimming in wi-fi.

311
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:38,960
We're living in a wi-fi soup.
Suppose something got inside it.

312
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:42,160
Suppose there was something
living in the wi-fi,

313
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:45,560
harvesting human minds, extracting them.

314
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:48,080
Imagine that.

315
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:52,360
Human souls trapped like flies
in the World Wide Web.

316
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:54,600
Stuck forever.

317
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:56,840
Crying out for help.

318
00:20:57,520 --> 00:20:58,760
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

319
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:00,760
Isn't that basically Twitter?

320
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:10,360
-What was that face for?
-A computer can hack another computer.

321
00:21:10,440 --> 00:21:13,040
A living, sentient computer...

322
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:16,320
Maybe that could hack people,
edit them, re-write them.

323
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:17,680
-Why would you say that?
-Because a few hours ago,

324
00:21:17,760 --> 00:21:19,480
you knew nothing about the internet.

325
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:24,320
-And you just made a joke about Twitter.
-Oh.

326
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:27,080
Oh!

327
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:28,600
Oh, that's weird.

328
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:32,120
I know all about computers now
in my head.

329
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:34,480
Where did all that come from?

330
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:35,720
You were uploaded for a while.

331
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:38,360
Wherever you were,
you brought something extra back.

332
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:43,360
Which I very much doubt
you're going to be allowed to keep.

333
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:47,200
(MAN WHIRRING)

334
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:53,400
You and me, inside that box now.

335
00:21:53,560 --> 00:21:56,600
-I'm sorry?
-Look, just get inside.

336
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:59,120
-Both of us?
-Trust me.

337
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:02,040
-You'll understand once we're in there.
-I bet I will!

338
00:22:02,120 --> 00:22:03,960
-Look, please...
-What is that box, anyway?

339
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:05,360
-Why have you got a box?
-Clara?

340
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:06,680
Is it like a snogging booth?

341
00:22:07,280 --> 00:22:09,520
-A what?
-Is that what you do? You bring a booth.

342
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:11,120
There's such a thing as too keen.

343
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,960
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

344
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:17,840
Clara, look around you.

345
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:30,360
What's going on?

346
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:32,120
What's happening?
Is the wi-fi switching on the lights?

347
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:34,040
DOCTOR: No, the people
are switching on the lights.

348
00:22:34,120 --> 00:22:36,160
The wi-fi's switching on the people.

349
00:22:39,080 --> 00:22:40,640
(LOUD WHIRRING)

350
00:22:42,560 --> 00:22:43,640
What is that thing?

351
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,880
DOCTOR: A walking base station.
You saw one earlier.

352
00:22:47,280 --> 00:22:48,320
I saw a little girl.

353
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:50,520
DOCTOR: They must have taken
an image from your subconscious,

354
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:52,600
thrown it back at you. Ah!

355
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:54,040
Active camouflage.

356
00:22:57,360 --> 00:22:58,680
They could be everywhere.

357
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:00,320
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

358
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:03,560
Doctor? Doctor.

359
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:07,920
CLARA: What's going on?

360
00:23:09,480 --> 00:23:11,680
MAHLER: Do we need another
London-wide activation?

361
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:14,960
We can't always pass it off as a riot.

362
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:18,800
Our lights are on,
everybody else's off. Why?

363
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:20,680
(AEROPLANE ENGINE ROARING)

364
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:22,760
Some planes have wi-fi.

365
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:24,640
I'm sorry?

366
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:26,320
We must be one hell
of a target right now.

367
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:27,600
(GASPS)

368
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:31,360
You, me, box. Now!

369
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:36,840
Yes, it's a spaceship!
Yes, it's bigger on the inside!

370
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:39,280
No, I don't have time to talk about it!

371
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:41,080
But... But...

372
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:43,440
-But... But it's...
-Shut up.

373
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:45,280
Please, short hops are difficult.

374
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:47,840
-Bigger on the inside. Actually bigger.
-(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

375
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:49,320
(THUD, CLARA EXCLAIMS)

376
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:51,640
-Right, come on!
-We're going to go back out there?

377
00:23:51,720 --> 00:23:55,480
We've moved.
It's a spaceship. We flew away.

378
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:58,320
-Away from the plane?
-Not exactly.

379
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:00,000
(BOTH SCREAM)

380
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,160
(GASPS) How did we get here?

381
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:03,880
It's a ship! I told you!

382
00:24:04,120 --> 00:24:05,840
It's all very stretchy!

383
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:08,280
Is this is the plane? The actual plane?
Are they all dead?

384
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:12,320
(GRUNTS)
Asleep. Switched off by the wi-fi.

385
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:13,760
Never mind them.

386
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:16,400
(BOTH GRUNTING)

387
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:20,920
(CLARA EXCLAIMS)

388
00:24:24,040 --> 00:24:25,880
What is going on? Is this real?

389
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:28,000
Please tell me what is happening!

390
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:30,520
I'm the Doctor.
I'm an alien from outer space.

391
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:32,080
I'm a thousand years old,
I've got two hearts

392
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:33,960
and I can't fly a plane! Can you?

393
00:24:34,040 --> 00:24:35,360
-No.
-Oh, fine.

394
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:37,640
Well, let's do it together.

395
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:40,400
(SHOUTING)

396
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:43,680
(BOTH SCREAMING)

397
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:52,400
(LAUGHING)

398
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:54,720
Whoo!

399
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:57,640
Oh!

400
00:24:58,200 --> 00:25:00,040
(PANTING)

401
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:02,200
Would a victory roll be too showy-offy?

402
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:04,320
-What the hell's going on?
-Well,

403
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:07,520
I'm blocking your wi-fi.
So you're waking up, for a start.

404
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:09,480
Tell you what, do you want to drive?

405
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:10,960
(PANTING)

406
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:13,960
(CLARA GASPS)

407
00:25:16,800 --> 00:25:19,200
I don't understand. What's happened?

408
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:22,200
That box. Where's it gone?

409
00:25:24,280 --> 00:25:26,480
Find that box!

410
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:32,680
Okay. When are you going to explain
to me what the hell is going on?

411
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:35,000
-Breakfast.
-(THUD)

412
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:38,400
-Right.
-What? I ain't waiting till breakfast.

413
00:25:39,080 --> 00:25:42,680
It's a time machine.
You never have to wait for breakfast.

414
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,640
(CROWD CHEERING)

415
00:25:46,080 --> 00:25:47,320
DOCTOR: Thank you! Thank you!

416
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:49,680
-(APPLAUSE)
-Yes, magic blue box.

417
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:53,920
All donations gratefully accepted.
Roll up! Roll up! Give us your dosh.

418
00:25:54,040 --> 00:25:56,000
Oh, pennies, pounds,
anything you've got.

419
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:57,880
Keep collecting.
We need enough for breakfast.

420
00:25:57,960 --> 00:25:59,600
Just popping back to the garage.

421
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:02,720
Garage?

422
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:13,320
This way.

423
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:16,960
So... So, this is tomorrow, then?
Tomorrow's come early.

424
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:21,200
No. It came at the usual time,
we just took a short cut.

425
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:23,160
-(CROWD APPLAUDS)
-Thank you. Thank you.

426
00:26:23,280 --> 00:26:25,440
Tomorrow, a camel!

427
00:26:25,760 --> 00:26:26,760
Clara.

428
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:35,600
What's happening?

429
00:26:35,720 --> 00:26:37,000
Blue box. Southbank.

430
00:26:37,080 --> 00:26:38,240
Definitely wasn't there
five minutes ago.

431
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:41,880
Are we sure this time?
Earl's Court was an embarrassment.

432
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:59,480
If you've got a flying time machine,
why are we on a motorbike?

433
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:01,800
I don't take the Tardis into battle.

434
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:03,000
Because it's made of wood?

435
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:05,120
Because it's the most powerful ship
in the universe

436
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:07,400
and I don't want it falling
into the wrong hands.

437
00:27:07,520 --> 00:27:09,520
Ah! Okay!

438
00:27:10,760 --> 00:27:12,160
(REVS ENGINE)

439
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,720
I do love London.

440
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:26,880
So many cameras.

441
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:34,680
CLARA: So if we can travel anywhere
in time and space,

442
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:37,160
why did we travel to the morning?
What's the point in that?

443
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:39,840
DOCTOR: Whoever's after us has spent
the whole night looking for us.

444
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:41,800
-Are you tired?
-Yes.

445
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:46,040
Well, then imagine how they feel.
They came the long way round.

446
00:27:47,080 --> 00:27:48,480
They've got to be close.

447
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:51,480
Definitely London,
going by the signal distribution.

448
00:27:51,560 --> 00:27:53,800
I can hack the lowest level
of their operating system

449
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:55,760
but I can't establish
a physical location,

450
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:57,040
their security's too good.

451
00:27:57,160 --> 00:27:58,160
-Are you an alien?
-I am.

452
00:27:58,320 --> 00:28:00,360
-Yes, okay with that?
-Fine, yeah.

453
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:01,920
-I think I'm fine.
-Oh, good.

454
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:04,040
So, what happens if you do find them?
What happens then?

455
00:28:04,120 --> 00:28:07,080
I don't know. I can't tell the future,
I just work there.

456
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:08,920
-You don't have a plan?
-Oh, you know what I always say

457
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:10,000
-about plans.
-What?

458
00:28:10,080 --> 00:28:12,080
-I don't have one.
-People always have plans.

459
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:13,600
(CLARA SLURPING)

460
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:16,160
Yes. Yes, I suppose they do.

461
00:28:16,240 --> 00:28:18,520
So, tell me, how long have you been
looking after those kids?

462
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:22,560
-About a year. Since their mum died.
-Okay.

463
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:24,520
Why you?

464
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:26,360
Family friend, I get that,
but there must have been others.

465
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:27,600
Why did it have to be you?

466
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:30,800
I mean, you don't
really seem like a nanny.

467
00:28:31,320 --> 00:28:32,960
-Give me.
-Ha!

468
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:34,840
Sorry. What?

469
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:36,560
You need to know
where they physically are,

470
00:28:36,640 --> 00:28:37,920
-their exact location?
-Yes.

471
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:39,800
- I can do it.
-0}, hang on. I need that.

472
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:41,400
You hacked the lower
operating system, yeah?

473
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:43,280
I'll have their physical location
in under five minutes.

474
00:28:43,360 --> 00:28:44,360
Pop off and get us a coffee.

475
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:45,560
If I can't find them,
you definitely can't.

476
00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:48,240
They uploaded me, remember?
I got computing stuff in my head.

477
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:50,280
-So do 1.
-I have insane hacking skills.

478
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:52,560
I'm from space and the future
with two hearts and...

479
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:54,120
27 brains.

480
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:55,920
And I can find them
in under five minutes plus photographs.

481
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:57,400
-Twenty-seven?
-Okay.

482
00:28:57,880 --> 00:28:59,800
-Slight exaggeration.
-Coffee. Go get.

483
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:01,840
Five minutes. I promise.

484
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:07,840
-The security is absolute.
-It's never about the security.

485
00:29:08,240 --> 00:29:10,560
It's about the people.

486
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:22,840
Why do you keep looking at me like that?

487
00:29:22,920 --> 00:29:26,640
Sorry, no, it's nothing. It's just...
You're a nanny. Isn't that a bit, well,

488
00:29:27,320 --> 00:29:29,400
-Victorian?
-Victorian?

489
00:29:29,480 --> 00:29:31,400
You're young, shouldn't you be doing,
you know, with the...

490
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:33,800
(STUTTERS) Young things with...

491
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:36,480
-young people.
-What, you mean like you, for instance?

492
00:29:36,600 --> 00:29:38,960
-Down, boy.
-No, no.

493
00:29:39,040 --> 00:29:41,440
I didn't... Oh, shut up!

494
00:29:42,040 --> 00:29:43,400
(GASPS) Shh...

495
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:46,600
(CHUCKLES)

496
00:29:51,520 --> 00:29:52,600
Ooh!

497
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:53,800
(SNIFFS)

498
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:56,600
Two more cappuccinos over there, please.

499
00:29:56,680 --> 00:29:58,200
(ITALIAN ACCENT) One moment, sir.

500
00:29:59,040 --> 00:30:00,320
(ENERGY PULSATES)

501
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:02,360
(BRITISH ACCENT) You realise
you haven't the slightest chance

502
00:30:02,440 --> 00:30:03,800
of saving your little friend?

503
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:05,200
(ENERGY PULSATES)

504
00:30:05,600 --> 00:30:06,600
I'm sorry, what?

505
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:08,440
(ITALIAN ACCENT)
I said, "One moment, sir."

506
00:30:08,520 --> 00:30:10,640
-(ENERGY PULSATES)
-(BRITISH ACCENT) I said,

507
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:15,160
"There is not the slightest chance
that you can save your little friend."

508
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:18,360
And don't annoy the old man,
he isn't, in fact, speaking.

509
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:21,280
-(ENERGY PULSATES)
-I'm speaking.

510
00:30:21,640 --> 00:30:22,920
Just using whatever's to hand.

511
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:27,840
Oh, she's rather pretty, isn't she?
Do you like her?

512
00:30:28,080 --> 00:30:30,240
I can make her like you, too,
if you want.

513
00:30:30,320 --> 00:30:31,480
(ENERGY PULSATES)

514
00:30:31,880 --> 00:30:34,120
You all right, sir?

515
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:35,760
Um, yes.

516
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:38,960
Yes. Fine.

517
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:50,760
-You okay?
-Sure. Setting up stuff.

518
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:52,600
-Need a username.
-Learning fast.

519
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:54,360
Clara Oswald for the win. Oswin!

520
00:30:56,280 --> 00:30:59,560
You could always call me Oswin,
seeing as that's my name.

521
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:04,600
(ENERGY PULSATES)

522
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:06,320
WAITRESS: Now, I want
you to take a look around.

523
00:31:06,760 --> 00:31:08,280
Go on. Have a little stroll.

524
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:11,360
And see how impossible
your situation is.

525
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:14,040
Go on. Take a look.

526
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:16,200
I do love showing off.

527
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:17,520
(ENERGY PULSATES)

528
00:31:20,720 --> 00:31:22,880
(NEWSREADER SPEAKING ON TV)

529
00:31:24,120 --> 00:31:25,240
(ENERGY PULSATES)

530
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:28,800
Just let me show you what control
of the wi-fi can do for one.

531
00:31:30,600 --> 00:31:31,760
-KIZLET: Stop!
-Stop!

532
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:40,960
I saw what you can do last night.

533
00:31:41,480 --> 00:31:42,920
And clear!

534
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:51,640
-(ENERGY PULSATES)
-We can hack anyone in the wi-fi

535
00:31:51,760 --> 00:31:53,160
once they've been exposed long enough.

536
00:31:53,240 --> 00:31:55,360
So there's one of your walking
base stations here, somewhere close?

537
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:57,760
-There's...
-...always someone close.

538
00:31:58,600 --> 00:32:00,520
We've released thousands into the world.

539
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:04,320
They home in on the wi-fi
like rats sniffing cheese.

540
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:09,200
(CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING)

541
00:32:11,640 --> 00:32:13,360
There's something up with the webcams.

542
00:32:16,400 --> 00:32:17,720
(CHUCKLES)

543
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:20,200
I don't know who you are
or why you are doing this

544
00:32:20,320 --> 00:32:22,040
but the people of this world
will not be harmed.

545
00:32:22,120 --> 00:32:23,680
They will not be controlled!
They will not be...

546
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:27,040
-The people of this world are in no...
-...danger whatsoever.

547
00:32:27,680 --> 00:32:31,280
My client requires a steady diet
of living human minds.

548
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:33,560
Healthy, free-range human minds.

549
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:37,480
He loves and cares for humanity.
In fact, he can't get enough of it.

550
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:39,080
It's obscene.

551
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:40,760
-It's murder.
-It's life.

552
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:43,480
The farmer tends his flock
like a loving parent.

553
00:32:43,960 --> 00:32:45,520
The abattoir is not a contradiction.

554
00:32:46,120 --> 00:32:48,320
No one loves cattle
more than Burger King.

555
00:32:49,640 --> 00:32:51,360
(CLEARS THROAT)

556
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:54,240
I'm sure of it. Someone's hacking
the webcams, all of them.

557
00:32:55,080 --> 00:32:56,360
Everybody check your webcams.

558
00:32:56,720 --> 00:32:58,480
But what would be the point,
taking mugshots of us lot?

559
00:33:04,400 --> 00:33:05,440
Who's on Facebook?

560
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:14,280
Uh, Bebo, MySpace? Habbo?

561
00:33:15,440 --> 00:33:16,520
(CHUCKLES)

562
00:33:17,160 --> 00:33:20,280
Put your hands down
if you didn't mention where you work.

563
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:35,720
This ends.

564
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:38,240
I'm going to end this today.

565
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:40,360
How? You don't even know...

566
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:41,880
...where we are.

567
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:43,880
Who's doing this? Who is your client?

568
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:47,640
Hmm? Answer me.

569
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:49,920
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

570
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:52,680
Miss Kizlet, we have a problem.

571
00:33:53,560 --> 00:33:55,120
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

572
00:33:56,040 --> 00:33:57,120
(SIGHS)

573
00:33:57,400 --> 00:33:59,480
I did it. I really did!

574
00:33:59,920 --> 00:34:01,560
I did it. I did it. I found them.

575
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:02,840
-You found them?
-The Shard.

576
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:04,000
They're in the Shard, floor 65.

577
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:06,080
-Floor 65.
-Are you listening to me, Doctor?

578
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:08,120
-I found them.
-I'm listening to you. You found them.

579
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:12,320
(WHIRRING)

580
00:34:33,040 --> 00:34:36,360
We've got her.
This time we've really got her.

581
00:34:37,680 --> 00:34:38,680
(SIGHS)

582
00:34:41,120 --> 00:34:42,640
Clara? Clara!

583
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:46,240
CLARA: Doctor? Doctor, help me.

584
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:48,080
IL.. I don't know where I am.

585
00:34:50,680 --> 00:34:52,200
I don't understand.

586
00:34:52,320 --> 00:34:53,600
Doctor, help me, please.

587
00:34:53,680 --> 00:34:56,400
I don't know where I am.
I don't know where I am/!

588
00:34:57,120 --> 00:34:58,960
I don't know where I am.

589
00:34:59,200 --> 00:35:01,280
Doctor, please.
Please help me. Please help me!

590
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:03,520
I don't know where I am.
I don't know where I am.

591
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:05,280
-(WHIRRING)
-Doctor, help me.

592
00:35:06,400 --> 00:35:07,840
I don't know where I am.

593
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:09,520
(ALL TALKING AT ONCE)

594
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:11,560
Should we pulp her
or keep her as a hostage?

595
00:35:11,680 --> 00:35:14,200
There's no point.
She's fully integrated now.

596
00:35:14,600 --> 00:35:17,280
She can't be downloaded again.
I'm sure he knows that.

597
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:19,360
I'm not sure he does.

598
00:35:20,040 --> 00:35:21,280
He's coming.

599
00:35:47,320 --> 00:35:49,360
We could stop him, I suppose.

600
00:35:49,440 --> 00:35:52,480
Why bother? Might be quite funny.

601
00:35:54,880 --> 00:35:56,280
(TYRES SCREECH)

602
00:35:58,040 --> 00:36:00,160
Really, Doctor? A motorbike?

603
00:36:00,320 --> 00:36:01,600
It hardly seems like you.

604
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:05,760
I rode this
in the Anti-Grav Olympics, 2074.

605
00:36:06,400 --> 00:36:07,560
I came last.

606
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:10,800
The building is in lockdown.
I'm afraid you're not coming in.

607
00:36:11,120 --> 00:36:13,280
Did you even hear the word "Anti-Grav"?

608
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:14,800
(ENGINE ROARS)

609
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:16,840
(ENGINE REVS)

610
00:36:18,520 --> 00:36:21,240
(TYRES SCREECHING, MOTORBIKE REVVING)

611
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:23,640
Seriously, he can do that?

612
00:36:24,040 --> 00:36:25,680
He can really actually do that?

613
00:36:26,360 --> 00:36:27,720
-Oh...
-...dear...

614
00:36:27,880 --> 00:36:28,880
...Lord.

615
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:40,360
(WHIRRING)

616
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:42,960
(GLASS SHATTERING)

617
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:44,520
I think that was your office.

618
00:36:44,600 --> 00:36:46,200
-(MOTORBIKE REVVING)
-Excuse me.

619
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:49,480
I believe there's someone to see me.

620
00:36:56,680 --> 00:36:58,160
KIZLET: Do come in.

621
00:36:59,480 --> 00:37:00,920
Download her.

622
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,360
Sorry about the draught.

623
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:05,600
Download her back into her body
right now.

624
00:37:06,120 --> 00:37:08,360
-I can't.
-Yes, you can.

625
00:37:09,120 --> 00:37:12,480
She's a fully integrated part
of the data cloud now,

626
00:37:12,560 --> 00:37:13,760
she can't be separated.

627
00:37:13,880 --> 00:37:16,440
Then download the entire cloud,
everyone you've trapped in there.

628
00:37:16,840 --> 00:37:18,120
You realise what would happen?

629
00:37:18,200 --> 00:37:20,920
Yes, those still with bodies
to go home to would be free.

630
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:23,120
A tiny number.

631
00:37:23,320 --> 00:37:24,760
Most would simply die.

632
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:27,200
They'd be released from a living hell.

633
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:31,520
It's the best you can do for them.
So give the order.

634
00:37:31,720 --> 00:37:35,320
-And why would I do that?
-'Cause I'm going to motivate you.

635
00:37:36,480 --> 00:37:37,920
Any second now.

636
00:37:39,720 --> 00:37:41,280
You ridiculous man.

637
00:37:41,560 --> 00:37:43,440
Why did you even come here?
Whatever for?

638
00:37:43,520 --> 00:37:44,680
I didn't.

639
00:37:44,760 --> 00:37:46,080
-What?
-I'm still in the cafe.

640
00:37:46,760 --> 00:37:48,200
I'm finishing my coffee.

641
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,000
Lovely spot.

642
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:51,240
What are you talking about?

643
00:37:51,320 --> 00:37:53,120
You hack people. But me...

644
00:37:54,160 --> 00:37:56,080
I'm old-fashioned.

645
00:37:57,560 --> 00:37:58,800
I hack technology.

646
00:37:59,720 --> 00:38:01,040
Here's your motivation.

647
00:38:01,720 --> 00:38:03,400
(WHIRRING)

648
00:38:07,720 --> 00:38:09,000
No!

649
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:10,920
No!

650
00:38:11,080 --> 00:38:12,680
-(ELECTRONIC BEEPING)
-KIZLET: Not me!

651
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:14,280
Not me!

652
00:38:19,280 --> 00:38:21,600
Put me back. Put me back!

653
00:38:21,840 --> 00:38:23,520
WOMAN 1: Can anybody hear me?
WOMAN 2: Where am I?

654
00:38:23,920 --> 00:38:25,400
Download me at once!

655
00:38:26,360 --> 00:38:29,560
That is an order. That is an order!

656
00:38:29,680 --> 00:38:31,200
(ALL TALKING, INDISTINCT)

657
00:38:31,400 --> 00:38:33,440
Mahler, she's fully integrated now.

658
00:38:33,520 --> 00:38:35,960
We'd have to download the entire cloud.

659
00:38:36,120 --> 00:38:38,600
-We can't do that.
-No, we can't.

660
00:38:39,320 --> 00:38:41,240
KIZLET: Download me!

661
00:38:57,840 --> 00:38:59,200
(TABLET WHIRRING)

662
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:01,840
KIZLET: Download me!

663
00:39:03,160 --> 00:39:04,640
(ENERGY PULSATES)

664
00:39:04,880 --> 00:39:06,400
Do what she says.

665
00:39:33,840 --> 00:39:35,960
(MURMURING) Mmm. Doctor?

666
00:39:45,640 --> 00:39:46,840
Doctor?

667
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:50,800
Doctor!

668
00:39:50,960 --> 00:39:52,240
You have no right to be in this office

669
00:39:52,320 --> 00:39:54,120
and I am demanding
that you leave at once!

670
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:56,280
OFFICER 1: This building
is under UNIT's control.

671
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:58,160
What is UNIT? I've never heard of UNIT.

672
00:39:58,240 --> 00:40:00,360
OFFICER 2: I suggest you calm down, sir.

673
00:40:02,280 --> 00:40:04,880
UNIT are here.
Friends of the Doctor, I presume?

674
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:07,760
Oh, old friends. Very old friends.

675
00:40:08,680 --> 00:40:11,160
Then I appear to have failed you,
Great Intelligence.

676
00:40:11,640 --> 00:40:14,240
I have feasted on many minds,
I have grown.

677
00:40:14,680 --> 00:40:17,640
But now it is time for you to reduce.

678
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:20,560
You've been whispering
in my ear so long

679
00:40:21,520 --> 00:40:24,040
I'm not sure I remember
what I was before.

680
00:40:24,840 --> 00:40:26,320
Goodbye, Miss Kizlet.

681
00:40:31,640 --> 00:40:33,080
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

682
00:40:39,760 --> 00:40:41,920
(HIGH-PITCHED TONE BLARING)

683
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:47,840
(ALL GROANING)

684
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:51,960
-MAN: Where am I?
-(ALL TALKING AT ONCE, INDISTINCT)

685
00:40:52,080 --> 00:40:54,920
(PANTING) I'm sorry.

686
00:40:55,280 --> 00:40:58,160
Where am I? What am I doing here?

687
00:40:58,240 --> 00:41:01,240
Are you soldiers? Uh, what's happening?

688
00:41:01,440 --> 00:41:03,720
-ALEXEI: How did I get here?
-Excuse me, where are the toilets?

689
00:41:04,200 --> 00:41:07,440
-The toilets?
-I'm here to fix the toilets, the gents.

690
00:41:09,160 --> 00:41:10,800
How long have I been here?

691
00:41:13,080 --> 00:41:14,640
OFFICER: Stay where you are!

692
00:41:14,720 --> 00:41:16,640
Ma'am, identify yourself.

693
00:41:19,920 --> 00:41:22,560
Where are my Mummy and Daddy?

694
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:26,880
They said they wouldn't be long.

695
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:30,480
Are they coming back?

696
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:34,600
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

697
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:37,160
(ALL CHATTERING, INDISTINCT)

698
00:41:46,680 --> 00:41:47,920
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

699
00:41:48,200 --> 00:41:49,240
Come in!

700
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:56,320
So...he comes back, does he?

701
00:41:57,640 --> 00:41:59,920
You didn't answer my question.

702
00:42:00,080 --> 00:42:01,400
What question?

703
00:42:03,760 --> 00:42:06,280
You don't seem like a nanny.

704
00:42:08,640 --> 00:42:10,080
I was going to travel.

705
00:42:11,120 --> 00:42:14,480
I came to stay for a week before I left
and during that week...

706
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:19,320
She died.

707
00:42:19,680 --> 00:42:21,720
So you're returning a favour then.

708
00:42:23,720 --> 00:42:26,160
But 101 places to see

709
00:42:26,840 --> 00:42:28,560
and you haven't been to any of them,
have you?

710
00:42:28,640 --> 00:42:30,120
That's why you keep the book.

711
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:33,040
I keep the book...

712
00:42:33,120 --> 00:42:34,680
because I'm still going.

713
00:42:37,200 --> 00:42:40,360
But you don't run out on the people
you care about.

714
00:42:40,440 --> 00:42:42,560
Wish I was more like that.

715
00:42:43,480 --> 00:42:45,200
You know,

716
00:42:45,760 --> 00:42:48,240
the thing about a time machine,

717
00:42:49,080 --> 00:42:51,960
you can run away all you like
and still be home in time for tea.

718
00:42:52,040 --> 00:42:54,200
So what do you say?

719
00:42:54,320 --> 00:42:56,200
Anywhere.

720
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:58,680
All of time and space
right outside those doors.

721
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:04,560
-Does this work? (LAUGHING)
-Eh?

722
00:43:04,640 --> 00:43:08,000
Is this actually what you do?
Do you just crook your finger

723
00:43:08,080 --> 00:43:10,320
and people just jump
in your snog box and fly away?

724
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:13,120
-It is not a snog box!
-I'll be the judge of that.

725
00:43:13,200 --> 00:43:15,120
Starting when?

726
00:43:20,720 --> 00:43:23,680
Come back tomorrow. Ask me again.

727
00:43:24,840 --> 00:43:28,160
-Why?
-Because tomorrow I might say yes.

728
00:43:28,240 --> 00:43:30,200
Sometime after 7:00 okay for you?

729
00:43:30,520 --> 00:43:32,680
It's a time machine.

730
00:43:32,840 --> 00:43:34,880
-Any time's okay.
-See you then.

731
00:43:35,240 --> 00:43:36,840
-Clara?
-Uh-huh?

732
00:43:36,920 --> 00:43:39,520
In your book, there was a leaf.

733
00:43:40,280 --> 00:43:42,000
Why?

734
00:43:42,480 --> 00:43:44,600
That wasn't a leaf.

735
00:43:45,720 --> 00:43:47,280
That was page one.

736
00:43:49,800 --> 00:43:51,160
It was...

737
00:43:55,120 --> 00:43:57,400
Right, then, Clara Oswald.

738
00:43:58,440 --> 00:44:01,240
Time to find out who you are.

739
00:44:06,480 --> 00:44:08,520
(WHOOSHING)

740
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:15,920
-What do you want to see?
-Something awesome.

741
00:44:16,080 --> 00:44:17,640
-DOCTOR: Akhaten.
-Can we see it? Up close?

742
00:44:18,160 --> 00:44:19,480
-Oh!
-You okay?

743
00:44:20,160 --> 00:44:21,240
-Have you seen her?
-Who?

744
00:44:21,320 --> 00:44:22,680
-I'm Merry Galel.
-(SCREAMING)

745
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:25,440
MAN: The Queen of Years.
MERRY: I'm the vessel of our history.

746
00:44:25,520 --> 00:44:26,760
-(GASPS)
-CLARA: What's happening?

747
00:44:26,840 --> 00:44:27,840
Is that supposed to happen?

748
00:44:28,080 --> 00:44:30,000
-Doctor!
-Don't walk away.

749
00:44:31,520 --> 00:44:32,760
CLARA: Merry!

750
00:44:34,080 --> 00:44:36,120
Stay back! I'm armed!
With a screwdriver.

751
00:44:36,200 --> 00:44:37,600
(GROWLING)

752
00:44:37,680 --> 00:44:39,800
DOCTOR: Grandfather's awake.

753
00:44:40,600 --> 00:44:42,520
You have it all!

